@dr.juerdotitsgo5119 The thing with Bond is, for me the same as what has happened to Doctor Who. Bond in the books is one thing and they are very different to the films. All the film Bonds before Craig were dark haired, and could do the suave charm as well as ruthless. They all fitted that tall dark and handsome description. Then they changed and abandoned all that with Craig. Short, blonde /mousey hair with blue eyes and no ability to do the charm, to be suave and the charisma of a brick.  It was too far removed from what we had. Add to that the loss of spectacle, fun and stunt action scenes or memorable villains, lairs and henchmen. There was just poker faced boredom. There is barely a thing from the Craig films I can remember. And not a single iconic moment like that Lotus going off the pier and becoming a submarine. No Volcano lairs, no mini helicopters, no jetpacks nothing that made you sit up and go - WOW that was cool! That looked good! 
So the whole series lost out to Mission Impossible for stunts action and spectacle, those films became more Bond than Bond.

Skyfall that people raved about has zero going on action wise apart from the opening on the train. The rest is sitting about talking, Bond gets shaved...Bond plays home alone in a mansion etc. It was supposed to be grounded and more realistic but it lost its sense of fun and adventure. Doctor Who was changed from its formula of a male Time lord from Gallifrey to a portal space baby who was a little girl. A woman, an ethnic gay bloke...it was a change too far and it killed it. If they dont go back to a tall dark handsome Bond with some action and adventure it will never have any chance of recovery.

